(Comment:) Tj
T* (The Docker image routes commands through a small entrypoint helper. Standard email CLI) Tj
T* (commands go to devnavigator.py, while monitor, toy-server, and toy-client run the Python) Tj
T* (monitor script. Mounting the repo to /workspace gives the container access to your local) Tj
T* (.env, files, and database folder.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Run the Python network monitor from the main Docker image) Tj
T* (    docker run --rm -it --network host -v "$\(pwd\):/workspace" devnavigator \\) Tj
T* (      monitor --interface auto --target 192.168.1.254 --samples 1) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Run the Python monitor continuously until you stop it) Tj
T* (    docker run --rm -it --network host -v "$\(pwd\):/workspace" devnavigator \\) Tj
T* (      monitor --interface auto --target 192.168.1.254 --loop) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (EXTRACT EMAILS FROM A FILE) Tj
T* (--------------------------) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Extract emails from any text-like file and store them in the database) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py extract-emails --file your_file.txt --store --source manual) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Example using the helper shell script) Tj
T* (    ./scripts/extraction/extract-emails.sh your_file.txt) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Comment:) Tj
T* (This path validates emails before saving them. Invalid addresses are skipped and shown in) Tj
T* (the output.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (IMPORT A STRUCTURED CSV) Tj
T* (-----------------------) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Import a CSV file that has an email column) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py import-contacts --file your_contacts.csv --source csv_upload) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (    # Import and mark contacts as approved/sendable immediately) Tj
T* (    python3 devnavigator.py import-contacts --file your_contacts.csv --source csv_upload) Tj
T* (    --consent) Tj
T* () Tj
T* () Tj
T* (Comment:) Tj
T* (Use this when your file already has columns like email,name,company,country.) Tj
T* () Tj
T* (CHECK WHAT WAS SAVED) Tj
T* (--------------------) Tj
ET
endstream
